ABUJA –  Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and Kano, which has become an area of concern, topped the list of new confirmed cases of COVID-19 pandemic on Sunday night. According to the update released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 170 new cases, bringing the total number of confirmed cases so far to 2,558 out of which Lagos and Kano reported 39 and 29 years new infections respectively. In addition, 400 patients have been discharged while 87 deaths have been recorded. The full report is as follows: 170 new cases of #COVID19; 39-Lagos29-Kano24-Ogun18-Bauchi15-Kaduna12-FCT12-Sokoto8-Katsina7-Borno3-Nasarawa2-Adamawa1-Oyo 2558 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in NigeriaDischarged: 400Deaths: 87 ABUJA - It was a harvest of deaths on Wednesday as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) gave its daily update on the COVID-19 pandemic as the virus continues its steady penetration in Nigeria.Though the NCDC as usual, didn't give details of the casualties but there was a steep… April 30, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Lagos State, the Federal Capital Territory, Kano and Oyo have spiked the number Nigeria's confirmed Coronavirus cases with the addition of 35 confirmed infections as at late Thursday night.Lagos State has 19 new infections with FCT contributing nine. Kano and Oyo have five and two new cases respectively… April 16, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - For the first time since the outbreak of the coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria, Kano has recorded the highest infection in a single day as reported by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Monday night. Kano had 23 new confirmed cases on Monday. In Lagos, which has… April 21, 2020 In "Top Stories"